gomodel:SYNGO_4103  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig5: phalloidin/rhodamine-coupled actin assay was used to detect new actin polymerization in the postsynaptic terminal. To investigate whether actin polymerization is mediated by ezrin, neurons treated with Urokinase-type plasminogen activator (uPA) were tested for new actin structures in the presence of ezrin siRNA. The area of newly formed actin in the presence of uPA shifted from 84.9 ± 1.51 μm2 to 38.8 ± 4.24 μm2 indicating that ezrin down-regulation abrogates the effect of uPA on actin formation.. Experimental description: C57BL/6J mice were used for the phalloidin/rhodamine-coupled actin assay. ezrin Accell siRNA and scramble siRNA was purchased from Dharmacon, Lafayette, CO." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4103" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

